33static void tty_term_override(struct tty_term *, const char *);
34static char *tty_term_strip(const char *);
35
36struct tty_terms tty_terms = LIST_HEAD_INITIALIZER(tty_terms);
37
38enum tty_code_type {
39 TTYCODE_NONE = 0,
40 TTYCODE_STRING,
41 TTYCODE_NUMBER,
42 TTYCODE_FLAG,
43};
44
45struct tty_code {
46 enum tty_code_type type;
47 union {
48 char *string;
49 int number;
50 int flag;
51 } value;
52};
53
54struct tty_term_code_entry {
55 enum tty_code_type type;
56 const char *name;
57};

270u_int
271tty_term_ncodes(void)
272{
273 return (nitems(tty_term_codes));
274}
275
276static char *
277tty_term_strip(const char *s)
278{
279 const char *ptr;
280 static char buf[BUFSIZ];
281 size_t len;
282
283 /* Ignore strings with no padding. */
284 if (strchr(s, '$') == NULL)
285 return (xstrdup(s));
286
287 len = 0;
288 for (ptr = s; *ptr != '\0'; ptr++) {
289 if (*ptr == '$' && *(ptr + 1) == '<') {
290 while (*ptr != '\0' && *ptr != '>')
291 ptr++;
292 if (*ptr == '>')
293 ptr++;
294 }
295
296 buf[len++] = *ptr;
297 if (len == (sizeof buf) - 1)
298 break;
299 }
300 buf[len] = '\0';
301
302 return (xstrdup(buf));
303}
304
305static void
306tty_term_override(struct tty_term *term, const char *override)
307{
308 const struct tty_term_code_entry *ent;
309 struct tty_code *code;
310 char *next, *s, *copy, *cp, *value;
311 const char *errstr;
312 u_int i;
313 int n, remove;
314
315 copy = next = xstrdup(override);
316
317 s = strsep(&next, ":");
318 if (s == NULL || next == NULL || fnmatch(s, term->name, 0) != 0) {
319 free(copy);
320 return;
321 }
322
323 while ((s = strsep(&next, ":")) != NULL) {
324 if (*s == '\0')
325 continue;
326 value = NULL;
327
328 remove = 0;
329 if ((cp = strchr(s, '=')) != NULL) {
330 *cp++ = '\0';
331 value = xstrdup(cp);
332 if (strunvis(value, cp) == -1) {
333 free(value);
334 value = xstrdup(cp);
335 }
336 } else if (s[strlen(s) - 1] == '@') {
337 s[strlen(s) - 1] = '\0';
338 remove = 1;
339 } else
340 value = xstrdup("");
341
342 if (remove)
343 log_debug("%s override: %s@", term->name, s);
344 else
345 log_debug("%s override: %s=%s", term->name, s, value);
346
347 for (i = 0; i < tty_term_ncodes(); i++) {
348 ent = &tty_term_codes[i];
349 if (strcmp(s, ent->name) != 0)
350 continue;
351 code = &term->codes[i];
352
353 if (remove) {
354 code->type = TTYCODE_NONE;
355 continue;
356 }
357 switch (ent->type) {
358 case TTYCODE_NONE:
359 break;
360 case TTYCODE_STRING:
361 if (code->type == TTYCODE_STRING)
362 free(code->value.string);
363 code->value.string = xstrdup(value);
364 code->type = ent->type;
365 break;
366 case TTYCODE_NUMBER:
367 n = strtonum(value, 0, INT_MAX, &errstr);
368 if (errstr != NULL)
369 break;
370 code->value.number = n;
371 code->type = ent->type;
372 break;
373 case TTYCODE_FLAG:
374 code->value.flag = 1;
375 code->type = ent->type;
376 break;
377 }
378 }
379
380 free(value);
381 }
382 free(s);
383}
384
385struct tty_term *
386tty_term_find(char *name, int fd, char **cause)
387{
388 struct tty_term *term;
389 const struct tty_term_code_entry *ent;
390 struct tty_code *code;
391 struct options_entry *o;
392 u_int size, i;
393 int n, error;
394 const char *s, *acs;
395
396 LIST_FOREACH(term, &tty_terms, entry) {
397 if (strcmp(term->name, name) == 0) {
398 term->references++;
399 return (term);
400 }
401 }
402 log_debug("new term: %s", name);
403
404 term = xmalloc(sizeof *term);
405 term->name = xstrdup(name);
406 term->references = 1;
407 term->flags = 0;
408 term->codes = xcalloc(tty_term_ncodes(), sizeof *term->codes);
409 LIST_INSERT_HEAD(&tty_terms, term, entry);
410
411 /* Set up curses terminal. */
412 if (setupterm(name, fd, &error) != OK) {
413 switch (error) {
414 case 1:
415 xasprintf(cause, "can't use hardcopy terminal: %s",
416 name);
417 break;
418 case 0:
419 xasprintf(cause, "missing or unsuitable terminal: %s",
420 name);
421 break;
422 case -1:
423 xasprintf(cause, "can't find terminfo database");
424 break;
425 default:
426 xasprintf(cause, "unknown error");
427 break;
428 }
429 goto error;
430 }
431
432 /* Fill in codes. */
433 for (i = 0; i < tty_term_ncodes(); i++) {
434 ent = &tty_term_codes[i];
435
436 code = &term->codes[i];
437 code->type = TTYCODE_NONE;
438 switch (ent->type) {
439 case TTYCODE_NONE:
440 break;
441 case TTYCODE_STRING:
442 s = tigetstr(ent->name);
443 if (s == NULL || s == (char *) -1)
444 break;
445 code->type = TTYCODE_STRING;
446 code->value.string = tty_term_strip(s);
447 break;
448 case TTYCODE_NUMBER:
449 n = tigetnum(ent->name);
450 if (n == -1 || n == -2)
451 break;
452 code->type = TTYCODE_NUMBER;
453 code->value.number = n;
454 break;
455 case TTYCODE_FLAG:
456 n = tigetflag(ent->name);
457 if (n == -1)
458 break;
459 code->type = TTYCODE_FLAG;
460 code->value.flag = n;
461 break;
462 }
463 }
464
465 /* Apply terminal overrides. */
466 o = options_get_only(global_options, "terminal-overrides");
467 if (options_array_size(o, &size) != -1) {
468 for (i = 0; i < size; i++) {
469 s = options_array_get(o, i);
470 if (s != NULL)
471 tty_term_override(term, s);
472 }
473 }
474
475 /* Delete curses data. */
476#if !defined(NCURSES_VERSION_MAJOR) || NCURSES_VERSION_MAJOR > 5 || \
477 (NCURSES_VERSION_MAJOR == 5 && NCURSES_VERSION_MINOR > 6)
478 del_curterm(cur_term);
479#endif
480
481 /* These are always required. */
482 if (!tty_term_has(term, TTYC_CLEAR)) {
483 xasprintf(cause, "terminal does not support clear");
484 goto error;
485 }
486 if (!tty_term_has(term, TTYC_CUP)) {
487 xasprintf(cause, "terminal does not support cup");
488 goto error;
489 }
490
491 /* These can be emulated so one of the two is required. */
492 if (!tty_term_has(term, TTYC_CUD1) && !tty_term_has(term, TTYC_CUD)) {
493 xasprintf(cause, "terminal does not support cud1 or cud");
494 goto error;
495 }
496
497 /* Figure out if we have 256 colours (or more). */
498 if (tty_term_number(term, TTYC_COLORS) >= 256 ||
499 tty_term_has(term, TTYC_RGB))
500 term->flags |= TERM_256COLOURS;
501
502 /*
503 * Terminals without xenl (eat newline glitch) wrap at at $COLUMNS - 1
504 * rather than $COLUMNS (the cursor can never be beyond $COLUMNS - 1).
505 *
506 * This is irritating, most notably because it is impossible to write
507 * to the very bottom-right of the screen without scrolling.
508 *
509 * Flag the terminal here and apply some workarounds in other places to
510 * do the best possible.
511 */
512 if (!tty_term_flag(term, TTYC_XENL))
513 term->flags |= TERM_EARLYWRAP;
514
515 /* Generate ACS table. If none is present, use nearest ASCII. */
516 memset(term->acs, 0, sizeof term->acs);
517 if (tty_term_has(term, TTYC_ACSC))
518 acs = tty_term_string(term, TTYC_ACSC);
519 else
520 acs = "a#j+k+l+m+n+o-p-q-r-s-t+u+v+w+x|y<z>~.";
521 for (; acs[0] != '\0' && acs[1] != '\0'; acs += 2)
522 term->acs[(u_char) acs[0]][0] = acs[1];
523
524 /* On terminals with xterm titles (XT), fill in tsl and fsl. */
525 if (tty_term_flag(term, TTYC_XT) &&
526 !tty_term_has(term, TTYC_TSL) &&
527 !tty_term_has(term, TTYC_FSL)) {
528 code = &term->codes[TTYC_TSL];
529 code->value.string = xstrdup("\033]0;");
530 code->type = TTYCODE_STRING;
531 code = &term->codes[TTYC_FSL];
532 code->value.string = xstrdup("\007");
533 code->type = TTYCODE_STRING;
534 }
535
536 /*
537 * On terminals with RGB colour (Tc or RGB), fill in setrgbf and
538 * setrgbb if they are missing.
539 */
540 if ((tty_term_flag(term, TTYC_TC) || tty_term_flag(term, TTYC_RGB)) &&
541 !tty_term_has(term, TTYC_SETRGBF) &&
542 !tty_term_has(term, TTYC_SETRGBB)) {
543 code = &term->codes[TTYC_SETRGBF];
544 code->value.string = xstrdup("\033[38;2;%p1%d;%p2%d;%p3%dm");
545 code->type = TTYCODE_STRING;
546 code = &term->codes[TTYC_SETRGBB];
547 code->value.string = xstrdup("\033[48;2;%p1%d;%p2%d;%p3%dm");
548 code->type = TTYCODE_STRING;
549 }
550
551 /* Log it. */
552 for (i = 0; i < tty_term_ncodes(); i++)
553 log_debug("%s%s", name, tty_term_describe(term, i));
554
555 return (term);
556
557error:
558 tty_term_free(term);
559 return (NULL);
560}
561
562void
563tty_term_free(struct tty_term *term)
564{
565 u_int i;
566
567 if (--term->references != 0)
568 return;
569
570 LIST_REMOVE(term, entry);
571
572 for (i = 0; i < tty_term_ncodes(); i++) {
573 if (term->codes[i].type == TTYCODE_STRING)
574 free(term->codes[i].value.string);
575 }
576 free(term->codes);
577
578 free(term->name);
579 free(term);
580}

582int
583tty_term_has(struct tty_term *term, enum tty_code_code code)
584{
585 return (term->codes[code].type != TTYCODE_NONE);
586}
587
588const char *
589tty_term_string(struct tty_term *term, enum tty_code_code code)
590{
591 if (!tty_term_has(term, code))
592 return ("");
593 if (term->codes[code].type != TTYCODE_STRING)
594 fatalx("not a string: %d", code);
595 return (term->codes[code].value.string);
596}

629int
630tty_term_number(struct tty_term *term, enum tty_code_code code)
631{
632 if (!tty_term_has(term, code))
633 return (0);
634 if (term->codes[code].type != TTYCODE_NUMBER)
635 fatalx("not a number: %d", code);

639int

641{
642 if (!tty_term_has(term, code))
643 return (0);
644 if (term->codes[code].type != TTYCODE_FLAG)
645 fatalx("not a flag: %d", code);

648
649const char *
650tty_term_describe(struct tty_term *term, enum tty_code_code code)
651{
652 static char s[256];
653 char out[128];
654
655 switch (term->codes[code].type) {
656 case TTYCODE_NONE:
657 xsnprintf(s, sizeof s, "%4u: %s: [missing]",
658 code, tty_term_codes[code].name);
659 break;
660 case TTYCODE_STRING:
661 strnvis(out, sizeof out, term->codes[code].value.string,
662 VIS_OCTAL|VIS_TAB|VIS_NL);
663 xsnprintf(s, sizeof s, "%4u: %s: (string) %s",
664 code, tty_term_codes[code].name,
665 out);
666 break;
667 case TTYCODE_NUMBER:
668 xsnprintf(s, sizeof s, "%4u: %s: (number) %d",
669 code, tty_term_codes[code].name,
670 term->codes[code].value.number);
671 break;
672 case TTYCODE_FLAG:
673 xsnprintf(s, sizeof s, "%4u: %s: (flag) %s",
674 code, tty_term_codes[code].name,
675 term->codes[code].value.flag ? "true" : "false");
676 break;
677 }
678 return (s);
679}
